<task id="UDSS-020" project="UI Dialog Shell Standardization">
  <metadata>
    <title>Extract PlaybookLibraryShell from AnalysisBuilder (~508 LOC)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <estimated-effort>8 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>shared-library, playbook, shell</tags>
    <dependencies>UDSS-001</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Extract the AnalysisBuilder App.tsx (~508 LOC) into a reusable PlaybookLibraryShell shared component. This shell encapsulates playbook browsing (tab 1), custom scope configuration (tab 2), and execution launching. Refactor all data access to use IDataService abstraction. This is the foundational task for Phase 3 — all other Phase 3 tasks depend on it. OK to update components/index.ts barrel here because this is the only extraction in Phase 3.</prompt>
  <role>Senior frontend developer with React and Fluent UI v9 expertise</role>
  <goal>PlaybookLibraryShell component extracted to @spaarke/ui-components/components/PlaybookLibraryShell/ with IDataService abstraction, exported from components barrel</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">IDataService abstraction required — no direct Xrm.WebApi calls in shared library components</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">All UI must use Fluent v9 tokens; dark mode must be supported; React 19 compatible</constraint>
    <constraint source="file-ownership">ONLY touch files in components/PlaybookLibraryShell/ folder and components/index.ts barrel</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/AnalysisBuilder/src/App.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/Playbook/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read AnalysisBuilder/src/App.tsx (~508 LOC) to understand the full component structure, state management, and data flow</step>
    <step id="2">Read shared Playbook components (PlaybookCardGrid, ScopeConfigurator, etc.) to understand existing shared abstractions</step>
    <step id="3">Create components/PlaybookLibraryShell/ directory in @spaarke/ui-components</step>
    <step id="4">Extract core functionality: playbook browsing (tab 1), custom scope configuration (tab 2), and execution launcher into PlaybookLibraryShell.tsx</step>
    <step id="5">Define IPlaybookLibraryShellProps interface: entityType, entityId, allowedPlaybookIds, mode, embedded, intent, onComplete, onClose, dataService, playbookService</step>
    <step id="6">Refactor all data access to use IDataService parameter — remove any direct Xrm.WebApi or fetch calls</step>
    <step id="7">Create local index.ts within PlaybookLibraryShell/ folder</step>
    <step id="8">Update components/index.ts barrel to export PlaybookLibraryShell</step>
    <step id="9">Run tsc to verify compilation and type correctness</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>PlaybookLibraryShell component exists in components/PlaybookLibraryShell/ with full browsing, scope config, and execution launch functionality</criterion>
    <criterion>IPlaybookLibraryShellProps interface defined with all required props (entityType, entityId, allowedPlaybookIds, mode, embedded, intent, onComplete, onClose, dataService, playbookService)</criterion>
    <criterion>No direct Xrm.WebApi or hardcoded fetch calls — all data access via IDataService</criterion>
    <criterion>Compiles successfully with tsc</criterion>
    <criterion>Exported from components/index.ts barrel</criterion>
    <criterion>Dark mode supported via Fluent v9 tokens</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
